{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CctHKhVqTWcHQcqEfSEXc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Elasticsearch cluster deployed and verified in the `elasticsearch` namespace, all using native Kubernetes resources (no operators/CRDs):\n\n- **ConfigMap** `es-config` — `elasticsearch.yml` with `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-0, es-1, es-2]`, `discovery.seed_hosts` pointing at the headless service, security/TLS enabled for both HTTP and transport layers (transport uses `verification_mode: certificate` since the shared cert's SANs don't cover per-pod DNS names).\n- **Services**: `es-discovery` (headless, port 9300, governs the StatefulSet for peer discovery) and `es-http` (ClusterIP, port 9200/HTTPS, as required).\n- **StatefulSet** `es` (3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` to avoid the ordered-readiness deadlock during initial cluster bootstrap), image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`, mounting `es-http-tls` for TLS material and `elastic-password` for the bootstrap `elastic` superuser.\n- **PodDisruptionBudget** `es-pdb` (minAvailable: 2).\n\nVerification:\n- All 3 pods (`es-0/1/2`) reached `1/1 Running`; `_cluster/health` reports `status: green`, `number_of_nodes: 3`, master elected (`es-1`).\n- Confirmed HTTPS reachability through `es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9200` both with and without full certificate-chain validation against `ca.crt` (hostname matches the cert's SAN wildcard).\n- Indexed a document, read it back, searched for it, and confirmed the primary/replica shards landed on two different nodes (`es-1`/`es-0`) with cluster status staying green — then cleaned up the test index."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":88,"cache_read_input_tokens":71301,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":88},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","